static <T> Stream<T> merge(Stream<? extends T>... streams)

      • interval

        static Stream<Integer> interval(long duration,
                                TimeUnit unit)
        Emits the integers 0, 1, 2, .... The first element is emitted immediately (0) and then the current thread is blocked with Thread.sleep for the given duration between further emissions. If you don't want the stream to start with 0 immediately then call interval(...).skip(1).
        Parameters:
        duration - sleep duration
        unit - unit of sleep duration
        Returns:
        stream with interval wait between emissions
